   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1862_02_10_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Bourjau_Hubener_Co_Shanghai_1.tif" n="envelope"/>
         <p>Per Martha + Theresa<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler +
                Co.<lb/>Nagasaki<lb/>⟨1862<lb/>Shanghai 10 Feb<lb/>Boujau
                Hübener+C<lb/>r[eceived]/18/2/62<lb/>b/19/2/62⟩</p>
         <pb facs="1862_02_10_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Bourjau_Hubener_Co_Shanghai_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <p>Per Martha + Theresa<lb/>Shanghai the 10th Feb. 62<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler +
                Co<lb/>Nagasaki<lb/>With reference to our<lb/> latest respectful letter from 4th of
                this month<lb/> we have not had the pleasure of hearing<lb/> from you since –<lb/>We
                are using this opportunity<lb/> to tell you that unfortunately<lb/> despite our
                continued efforts<lb/> we still have not managed to <lb/> charter coal ships for
                you<lb/> + that we generally see<lb/> little prospect to succeed for <lb/> you soon.
                – The coal price<lb/>has now reached such a <lb/> high level (for<lb/>Japan Ts 9 per
                ton + even a little<lb/>more could easily be<lb/> achieved). Thus we are even more
                <lb/>sorry that we were not more fortunate <lb/>in operating for you _ In the
                meantime<lb/> you should endeavour to secure<lb/>some space in the ships
                sailing<lb/> there in order to make at<lb/> least some profit from the <lb/> good
                prices here, meanwhile <lb/>we will continue with our<lb/> best efforts on your
                behalf + hopefully<lb/>with more success soon. –<lb/>Apart from this, there is
                nothing new<lb/> to report, the business is very quiet. <lb/>Your p.p. Bourjau
                Hübener + Co.<lb/>Ernst Behre</p>
         <pb facs="1862_02_10_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Bourjau_Hubener_Co_Shanghai_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1862_02_10_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Bourjau_Hubener_Co_Shanghai_4.tif" n="4"/>
      </body>
